{"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "schema", "document", "Document"], "kwargs": {"metadata": {"doc_id": "11df44989a1a0c89b21131f42b0a8614", "source": "NexaCorp Policy Handbook v5.2", "part": "2. Code of Business Conduct & Ethics", "section": "2.1 Ethical Standards & Expectations", "subsection": "2.1.1 General Principles", "raw_content": "All NexaCorp personnel are expected to: Act with honesty, transparency, and fairness in all professional dealings, including interactions with clients, vendors, regulators, and colleagues. Comply fully with all applicable laws, regulations, and NexaCorp policies in every jurisdiction where the company operates. Promptly report actual or suspected violations of this Code through the designated reporting channels (see Section 2.5). Exercise sound judgment and seek guidance when uncertain about the ethical or legal implications of a business decision. Avoid actions that could create even the appearance of impropriety, regardless of intent.", "type": "text"}, "page_content": "Part: 2. Code of Business Conduct & Ethics\n            Section: 2.1 Ethical Standards & Expectations\n            Subsection: 2.1.1 General Principles\n            All NexaCorp personnel are expected to: Act with honesty, transparency, and fairness in all professional dealings, including interactions with clients, vendors, regulators, and colleagues. Comply fully with all applicable laws, regulations, and NexaCorp policies in every jurisdiction where the company operates. Promptly report actual or suspected violations of this Code through the designated reporting channels (see Section 2.5). Exercise sound judgment and seek guidance when uncertain about the ethical or legal implications of a business decision. Avoid actions that could create even the appearance of impropriety, regardless of intent.", "type": "Document"}}